name: Fraternity Blues
author: Townes Van Zandt
lyrics:
I decided to improve my social station
I joined a fraternal organization
Tucked in my shirt, signed on the line
Right away they set about to improve my mind
The car I drove, the books I read,
the food I ate, the booze I drank,
the girls I took out,
My breath
They said "kid we don't much like the way you walk
and you're gonna have to change the way you talk"
They said "your dress is kinda sluochy

You got to bubble with enthusiamm,
I started bubblin'

how that's gonna' make me any more of a man

I can rip through that son-of-a-beta backwards in 5 seconds
Then they hit me with some pretty bad news
Concerning the payment of monthly dues
I never did know where that money went
but I paid it
I'm no trouble causer and besides, I figured that's life
If you want good friends, they're gonna cost ya
Well it finally got to be party time
I got a great big ole jug of wine
I went back to the house in about an hour
Brandy alexanders and frozen dqauaris
Reciting the greek alphabet to one another
I could see I was gonna have to do my very best
To get myself out of that fraternity mess
So I stood right there outside the door
And I chugged that wine like never before
Walked inside and bubbled -
all over a couple of their dates
So now everything is back to normal again
but there is still lots of room for improvement, friend
Of course that fraternity stuff's too much for me
Next time I'm gonna' join a sorotity
And really give em something to bubble about

lyrics:

But I didn't have the bus fare to Kentucky

I didn't have the bus fare to Kentucky
And that old Grey Dog won't let me ride for free.
I can't afford to go first class so I'll make it the best I can

Kentucky your bluegrass bridges and your valleys call to me
Kentucky I'm comin' home to stay
Kentucky I'm a comin' home I'll never leave you anymore...
